More than 100 mandrax tablets and 21 tik 'bankies' were confiscated on Tuesday. CAPE TOWN - Police has arrested a highflyer for drugs to the value of R7,000 at the taxi rank in Knysna. The operation was conducted after information on drug-related activities were received from a member of the public. More than 100 mandrax tablets and 21 tik “bankies” were confiscated on Tuesday. The police’s Chris Spies said: “The suspect is in custody and was charged for dealing drugs. He will remain in custody until he appears in court.”